All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
ACOAnt
The ACOAnt class is responsible for the ant's behaviour.
Colony
The Colony class is responsible for creating the ants and adding them to the queue.
Constant
The Constant class represents the constant values used in the program.
Event
The Event class represents an abstract event in a priority event queue.
EventEnd
The EventEnd class represents an event that marks the end of the simulation.
EventEvaporate
The EventEvaporate class represents an event for evaporating pheromones between two nodes in a graph.
EventMove
The EventMove class represents an event for moving an ACOAnt in the graph.
EventObservation
The EventObservation class represents an event that performs an observation at a specific time during the simulation.
FeromonasCycle
The FeromonasCycle class is responsible for calculating the concentration of pheromones and places them on the edges traveled by the ant.
FeromonasGraph
The FeromonasGraph class extends the Graph class and provides additional functionality for the pheromones graph.
Graph
The Graph class represents a graph.
Interface
The Interface class is responsible for executing the program based on user input.
Observation
The Observation class represents an observation responsible for "observing" the events and printing the results
Queue
The Queue class represents a queue of events.
WeightedGraph
The WeightedGraph class represents a graph with the weight of each edge.
